<TITLE> Bhuiyan backers start crucial meeting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 15 (bdnews24.com) -- BNP "reformists" started a meeting Saturday afternoon to announce the next course of action to hold the troubled party together. The BNP leaders, led by Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan, sat at the meeting in Gulshan. Mofiqul Hasan Tripti, a backer of Bhuiyan, has said that as many as 130 leaders are with the group. The meeting comes amid a broader divide in the BNP, which was laid open after party chairperson Khaleda Zia was arrested on Sept 3. The crisis deepened in the troubled BNP after Khaleda expelled Bhuiyan from the pary and installed Khandaker Delwar Hossain as secetary general. bd
